1
00:00:28,620 --> 00:00:30,420
Don't drop crumbs on the tablet.

2
00:00:30,930 --> 00:00:33,130
It's hard to wipe off the grease stains.

3
00:00:33,550 --> 00:00:34,820
Got it.

4
00:00:45,670 --> 00:00:47,070
I told you to stop eating.

5
00:00:48,580 --> 00:00:49,910
I have something to say.

6
00:00:50,070 --> 00:00:50,670
What is it?

7
00:00:51,370 --> 00:00:53,030
Before you started dating me,

8
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:55,930
did you spend Christmas here alone

9
00:00:56,450 --> 00:00:57,870
or

10
00:00:57,870 --> 00:00:59,100
with someone else?

11
00:01:03,160 --> 00:01:04,680
Why bring up the past?

12
00:01:05,780 --> 00:01:08,840
Don't ask about things
that have nothing to do with you.

13
00:01:09,900 --> 00:01:11,900
As your boyfriend,
I can't ask that?

14
00:01:18,170 --> 00:01:19,280
I told you to stop eating.

15
00:01:19,280 --> 00:01:20,680
I'm not going to.

16
00:01:24,480 --> 00:01:26,539
You know I don't eat things like this.

17
00:01:53,500 --> 00:01:54,700
It tastes bad.

18
00:01:54,700 --> 00:01:56,350
It's delicious.

19
00:01:56,350 --> 00:01:58,220
No, it's not. What's good about this?

20
00:01:58,220 --> 00:01:59,200
Have one more.

21
00:01:59,200 --> 00:02:00,480
No.

22
00:02:00,480 --> 00:02:01,280
Just one more.

23
00:02:08,440 --> 00:02:09,220
Wait.

24
00:02:10,430 --> 00:02:11,480
I have an idea.

25
00:02:11,860 --> 00:02:12,520
Look here.

26
00:02:19,820 --> 00:02:21,290
You look so funny.

27
00:02:22,190 --> 00:02:22,790
Let me see.

28
00:02:24,100 --> 00:02:25,300
Isn't it a good photo?

29
00:02:25,590 --> 00:02:26,650
What are you doing?

30
00:02:27,160 --> 00:02:28,440
Only you look good in this photo.

31
00:02:28,440 --> 00:02:29,470
What do you mean?

32
00:02:29,470 --> 00:02:30,230
I'm going to delete it.

33
00:02:30,230 --> 00:02:31,100
Why?

34
00:02:31,100 --> 00:02:32,660
I look so ugly in it.

35
00:02:32,660 --> 00:02:33,910
Wait.

36
00:02:33,910 --> 00:02:35,170
I'm going to delete it.

37
00:02:53,230 --> 00:02:55,230
Merry Christmas!

38
00:02:58,840 --> 00:02:59,790
Who is he?

39
00:03:00,250 --> 00:03:01,400
Why are you here?

40
00:03:01,630 --> 00:03:02,750
It's Christmas.

41
00:03:03,050 --> 00:03:04,920
I'm here to celebrate with you.

42
00:03:08,670 --> 00:03:10,520
I didn't ask you to come.

43
00:03:10,790 --> 00:03:11,560
Wow.

44
00:03:11,560 --> 00:03:12,560
Look at that face.

45
00:03:12,680 --> 00:03:13,230
Hey.

46
00:03:13,480 --> 00:03:14,530
You're so cold.

47
00:03:15,490 --> 00:03:16,420
Hello.

48
00:03:16,420 --> 00:03:17,680
You're Haejun, right?

49
00:03:17,880 --> 00:03:19,680
Jaehun told me a lot about you.

50
00:03:20,910 --> 00:03:22,570
You're cuter than I expected.

51
00:03:23,620 --> 00:03:25,120
Can I come in?

52
00:03:27,550 --> 00:03:29,680
As if you ever asked for my permission.

53
00:03:31,380 --> 00:03:33,579
One should drink mulled wine
in winter.

54
00:03:34,670 --> 00:03:36,740
I know there are a lot of good wines here,

55
00:03:36,740 --> 00:03:38,220
but I picked this myself—

56
00:03:38,220 --> 00:03:39,750
it has a different meaning.

57
00:03:40,950 --> 00:03:41,680
But

58
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:43,329
isn't this wine really expensive?

59
00:03:43,329 --> 00:03:44,450
He's rich.

60
00:03:44,450 --> 00:03:46,250
Oh, right!

61
00:03:46,250 --> 00:03:48,230
I forgot something in my car.

62
00:03:49,640 --> 00:03:50,220
Hey.

63
00:03:52,560 --> 00:03:53,810
Go get it.

64
00:03:53,810 --> 00:03:55,230
The car is parked at the door.

65
00:03:55,230 --> 00:03:56,360
Go get it.

66
00:04:00,380 --> 00:04:01,240
Are you crazy?

67
00:04:02,220 --> 00:04:03,040
You go.

68
00:04:03,410 --> 00:04:04,110
You go.

69
00:04:07,440 --> 00:04:08,650
Let me get that.

70
00:04:14,170 --> 00:04:16,430
Go get it.
Your friend wants you to get it.

71
00:04:17,450 --> 00:04:18,350
Just once.

72
00:04:19,410 --> 00:04:19,860
Okay?

73
00:04:23,150 --> 00:04:24,610
Don't do anything stupid.

74
00:04:32,870 --> 00:04:34,130
You're Haejun, right?

75
00:04:35,220 --> 00:04:36,420
I'm Kang Soohyung.

76
00:04:36,820 --> 00:04:37,920
Jaehun and I

77
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:39,920
have been friends since childhood.

78
00:04:44,540 --> 00:04:46,840
It's not easy for you

79
00:04:46,840 --> 00:04:48,840
to be here today.

80
00:05:00,980 --> 00:05:01,780
Hyung!

81
00:05:12,080 --> 00:05:13,260
It really suits you.

82
00:05:15,750 --> 00:05:16,480
Let's wear it together.

83
00:05:16,480 --> 00:05:18,240
I bought it for Christmas.

84
00:05:25,790 --> 00:05:27,340
The size is just right too.

85
00:05:32,180 --> 00:05:34,040
Why do you like clothes like this?

86
00:05:36,010 --> 00:05:37,230
What do you mean?

87
00:06:11,100 --> 00:06:13,100
I've fulfilled your request.

88
00:06:14,310 --> 00:06:15,640
It's my turn now.

89
00:06:16,810 --> 00:06:17,910
No.

90
00:06:19,270 --> 00:06:20,720
Why not?

91
00:06:22,400 --> 00:06:23,930
You said you'd listen to me.

92
00:06:33,960 --> 00:06:35,080
Why not?

93
00:06:37,720 --> 00:06:38,500
Huh?

94
00:06:39,890 --> 00:06:42,090
I've fulfilled all your requirements.

95
00:06:45,030 --> 00:06:46,310
Jaehun

96
00:06:46,780 --> 00:06:49,080
has high self-esteem.

97
00:06:50,550 --> 00:06:51,850
He didn't tell you

98
00:06:52,370 --> 00:06:53,630
about his past, right?

99
00:06:57,210 --> 00:06:58,690
Don't you want to know

100
00:06:59,560 --> 00:07:00,990
how he became a sadist?

101
00:07:04,050 --> 00:07:05,320
When Jaehun was a kid,

102
00:07:05,870 --> 00:07:08,200
he suffered severe
abuse from his family.

103
00:07:10,130 --> 00:07:12,130
His father pushed him into the water

104
00:07:12,180 --> 00:07:13,510
to stop him from crying.

105
00:07:14,530 --> 00:07:16,530
In order to erase that memory,

106
00:07:16,970 --> 00:07:19,430
he decided to be the one
in control of others.

107
00:07:24,220 --> 00:07:26,020
Aren't you going to have dinner
before you leave?

108
00:07:26,020 --> 00:07:27,300
Look at his face.

109
00:07:27,730 --> 00:07:29,660
He was clearly telling me to leave.

110
00:07:33,130 --> 00:07:34,600
Remember

111
00:07:35,430 --> 00:07:36,909
what I just said.

112
00:07:38,680 --> 00:07:39,900
Be careful,

113
00:07:40,280 --> 00:07:40,930
kid.

114
00:09:32,770 --> 00:09:33,870
Don't move.

115
00:09:35,570 --> 00:09:36,920
This is perfect.

116
00:09:41,010 --> 00:09:42,550
Shall I take off my clothes too?

117
00:09:42,550 --> 00:09:43,250
No.

118
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:45,800
This is perfect.

119
00:10:07,030 --> 00:10:07,730
Weird.

120
00:10:09,830 --> 00:10:10,630
What's wrong?

121
00:10:11,850 --> 00:10:13,850
I can draw you.

122
00:10:15,110 --> 00:10:16,710
But I can't draw

123
00:10:17,340 --> 00:10:19,520
the emotions in your eyes.

124
00:10:20,860 --> 00:10:21,860
It feels like

125
00:10:22,970 --> 00:10:24,970
it's covered in fog.

126
00:10:41,010 --> 00:10:41,930
Stop drawing.

127
00:10:48,300 --> 00:10:51,100
You need to experience it yourself
to draw it well.

128
00:11:19,300 --> 00:11:20,330
Lean forward.

129
00:12:28,470 --> 00:12:29,700
Can you see the emotions

130
00:12:29,700 --> 00:12:30,700
in my eyes?

131
00:12:37,880 --> 00:12:38,910
They're burning.

132
00:12:42,470 --> 00:12:43,950
What about the fog?

133
00:12:46,690 --> 00:12:47,540
It's gone.

134
00:12:58,840 --> 00:13:00,270
Now, my name

135
00:13:01,150 --> 00:13:02,250
is on your body.

136
00:13:11,620 --> 00:13:12,680
Oh no, my painting.

137
00:13:15,780 --> 00:13:17,780
It's just a painting.

138
00:13:19,220 --> 00:13:21,350
I have to submit this to the professor.

139
00:13:21,500 --> 00:13:23,500
I drew you so well too.

140
00:13:23,970 --> 00:13:26,030
Don't worry. You have plenty of time.

141
00:13:26,330 --> 00:13:27,860
No matter how much you draw,

142
00:13:29,480 --> 00:13:30,660
I'll be by your side.

143
00:13:35,400 --> 00:13:36,930
No matter how much you draw,

144
00:13:38,330 --> 00:13:39,600
I'll be by your side.

145
00:14:01,780 --> 00:14:02,490
What now?

146
00:14:08,510 --> 00:14:09,310
Got it.

147
00:14:09,320 --> 00:14:10,450
I'll be right there.

148
00:14:14,990 --> 00:14:16,160
I'll be right back.

149
00:14:16,660 --> 00:14:17,590
Go take a shower.

150
00:14:49,740 --> 00:14:51,270
If it's nothing important,

151
00:14:51,530 --> 00:14:52,580
I'm leaving.

152
00:14:54,140 --> 00:14:56,140
I don't know if this is important,

153
00:14:57,190 --> 00:14:58,650
but you'll be interested.

154
00:15:01,170 --> 00:15:01,830
Have a seat.

155
00:15:13,530 --> 00:15:14,100
Did I

156
00:15:14,790 --> 00:15:16,040
disturb you?

157
00:15:20,500 --> 00:15:21,210
No.

158
00:15:22,850 --> 00:15:24,380
As long as there is someone,

159
00:15:25,050 --> 00:15:26,310
I can have fun anytime.

160
00:15:27,060 --> 00:15:28,480
How nice, to have

161
00:15:28,480 --> 00:15:30,340
a long-term bed partner.

162
00:15:31,810 --> 00:15:32,870
You're one to talk.

163
00:15:33,980 --> 00:15:35,360
People queue up for you.

164
00:15:36,480 --> 00:15:38,280
Well, they have to be to my taste.

165
00:15:42,930 --> 00:15:44,080
So what is it?

166
00:15:45,410 --> 00:15:47,140
I went to Gyeonggi today,

167
00:15:47,640 --> 00:15:49,100
so I dropped by your house.

168
00:15:52,070 --> 00:15:53,930
Your housekeeper has gotten old.

169
00:15:55,300 --> 00:15:56,100
But

170
00:15:56,740 --> 00:15:58,070
he still remembers you.

171
00:15:59,860 --> 00:16:00,990
He said he found this

172
00:16:01,510 --> 00:16:03,240
when he was cleaning your room.

173
00:16:44,750 --> 00:16:45,880
How should I search?

174
00:16:49,300 --> 00:16:51,420
[Han Jaehun]

175
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:55,300
[Han Jaehun]

176
00:16:59,090 --> 00:17:01,550
I can't find anything
when I search his name.

177
00:17:03,900 --> 00:17:05,470
Why is nothing coming up?

178
00:17:36,670 --> 00:17:38,320
I went to Gyeonggi today,

179
00:17:38,760 --> 00:17:40,220
so I dropped by your house.

180
00:17:43,150 --> 00:17:45,010
Your housekeeper has gotten old.

181
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:54,400
He sewed and cleaned it himself,

182
00:18:55,690 --> 00:18:57,350
and kept it until now.

183
00:18:59,160 --> 00:19:02,120
He thought you might come back someday.

184
00:19:03,540 --> 00:19:04,460
This is...

185
00:19:07,150 --> 00:19:08,770
The housekeeper said

186
00:19:09,650 --> 00:19:11,300
he mended all the broken parts

187
00:19:11,300 --> 00:19:12,740
on it.

188
00:19:13,310 --> 00:19:15,570
He cleaned it regularly every month too.

189
00:19:16,010 --> 00:19:17,310
He thought

190
00:19:17,550 --> 00:19:19,310
you might come back someday.

191
00:20:44,700 --> 00:20:46,230
Has my mom been well

192
00:20:47,500 --> 00:20:48,510
since then?

193
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:53,370
From what I heard,

194
00:20:54,660 --> 00:20:56,660
she moved abroad alone.

195
00:20:59,470 --> 00:21:01,470
But she passed away.

196
00:21:06,660 --> 00:21:07,680
But...

197
00:21:08,670 --> 00:21:10,220
I heard that she lived

198
00:21:10,220 --> 00:21:11,820
quite a free life since then.

199
00:21:25,920 --> 00:21:26,680
Got it.

200
00:21:27,910 --> 00:21:29,040
Thank you so much.

201
00:21:30,550 --> 00:21:32,370
If you want to thank me,

202
00:21:32,650 --> 00:21:34,650
you should show some appreciation.

203
00:21:35,690 --> 00:21:37,340
What do you want?

204
00:21:38,120 --> 00:21:39,820
For example,

205
00:21:40,280 --> 00:21:42,160
introduce me

206
00:21:46,420 --> 00:21:48,420
to that kid in your house.

207
00:21:53,760 --> 00:21:55,020
Don't touch him.

208
00:21:55,770 --> 00:21:57,520
Okay, okay.

209
00:21:59,550 --> 00:22:01,550
I don't have those thoughts for now.

210
00:22:02,980 --> 00:22:04,980
I'll tell you when I do.

211
00:22:13,600 --> 00:22:14,500
Bye.

212
00:22:24,120 --> 00:22:27,010
Oops, I got him good.

213
00:22:28,680 --> 00:22:29,990
Kim Haejun,

214
00:22:30,450 --> 00:22:32,290
what are you going to do now?

215
00:23:32,450 --> 00:23:33,370
Mom.

216
00:23:36,600 --> 00:23:37,860
Dad and I...

217
00:23:38,980 --> 00:23:39,800
No.

218
00:23:42,300 --> 00:23:43,380
Am I that much like

219
00:23:45,840 --> 00:23:47,840
that person?

220
00:23:50,710 --> 00:23:53,380
Is that why you never came back?

221
00:25:01,820 --> 00:25:02,680
Jaehun-hyung!

222
00:25:03,770 --> 00:25:04,920
Are you in there?

223
00:25:07,420 --> 00:25:08,350
Are you okay?

224
00:25:09,890 --> 00:25:11,320
I smell smoke.

225
00:25:11,890 --> 00:25:13,710
I'm fine, Haejun.

226
00:25:14,810 --> 00:25:15,740
Go to sleep.

227
00:25:24,650 --> 00:25:25,480
Okay.

228
00:26:30,190 --> 00:26:31,120
Let me

229
00:26:33,690 --> 00:26:34,740
warm you up.

230
00:26:58,030 --> 00:26:58,830
Do you like it?

231
00:27:36,570 --> 00:27:49,980
[Tide of Love 2]

232
00:29:09,080 --> 00:29:17,690
[Tide of Love 2]
